UNITED STATES of America, Appellee, v. Max KELMAN, Appellant. No. 475. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. July 9, 1934. James E. Cuff, of Rochester, N. Y., for appellant. Richard H. Templeton, of Buffalo, N. Y. (Joseph J. Doran, Asst. U. S. Atty., of counsel), for the United States.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
